    assessmentFindings: ["Elevated LDL and/or triglycerides on lipid panel (usually asymptomatic)", "Xanthomas: tendon (Achilles, extensor tendons), tuberous (elbows, knees), eruptive (hypertriglyceridemia)", "Xanthelasma: yellowish plaques on eyelids", "Corneal arcus: grey-white ring around cornea (<45 years suggests FH)", "Premature ASCVD events (MI, stroke, PAD)"],
