    pearls: ["Hypertensive cardiomyopathy progression: concentric LVH → diastolic dysfunction (HFpEF) → eccentric dilation → systolic dysfunction (HFrEF)", "S4 gallop is the hallmark of diastolic dysfunction — represents atrial contraction against a stiff, non-compliant ventricle", "ACEi/ARBs are PREFERRED for LVH regression — they have direct anti-remodeling effects beyond BP lowering", "LVH is an INDEPENDENT risk factor for sudden cardiac death, atrial fibrillation, and stroke", "AVOID NSAIDs in hypertensive cardiomyopathy/HF — they cause sodium retention, volume expansion, and worsen HF", "Daily weights are essential: >2 lbs overnight or >5 lbs in a week = fluid retention requiring intervention"],
