    pearls: ["HCM murmur INCREASES with Valsalva/standing (decreased preload) and DECREASES with squatting (increased preload) — OPPOSITE to most murmurs", "HCM is the #1 cause of sudden cardiac death in young athletes — screen with history, physical exam, and ECG", "AVOID in HCM: dehydration, inotropes (digoxin, dobutamine), vasodilators, excessive diuretics — all worsen dynamic LVOT obstruction", "Mavacamten is the first targeted therapy — directly reduces sarcomere hypercontractility", "ICD for primary prevention of SCD in high-risk patients: wall thickness ≥30 mm, family SCD, unexplained syncope, NSVT, abnormal exercise BP response", "Deep Q waves on ECG in HCM represent septal hypertrophy, NOT myocardial infarction"],
